SIMPLE: predicable
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predicable
<hw>Pred"i*ca*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧dicable</ets>, L. <ets>praedicabilis</ets> praiseworthy.
See <er>Predicate</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being predicated or
affirmed of something; affirmable; attributable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predicable</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Predicable
<hw>Pred"i*ca*ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Anything
affirmable of another; especially, a general attribute or notion as
affirmable of, or applicable to, many individuals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>One of the five most general
relations of attributes involved in logical arrangements, namely, genus,
species, difference, property, and accident.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predicament</ent>⟦br⟧
